name: Leon Boedels
comments: He was a humorist and music-hall singer and one of the most popular artists of his time in Amsterdam. He was born in Rotterdam where he began his career in 1883. His first performance as a variety artist took place in Rotterdam in December 1884 – a six-week engagement. He then traveled as a singer from one city to another, from fair to fair, often with the well-known Jewish musician family Culp from Groningen, or with the Amsterdam Specialties Company Frits van Haarlem. Around 1890 he lived in Amsterdam. In 1892 the Theater Flora was founded in Amsterdam by the German-born Franz Nöggerath, where Leon performed in variety shows as a verse singer. Song about current topics, the lyrics of which were sold during the break. In May 1894 he even became director and resident humorist at Flora. Around 1900 Boedels adapted the well-known German tune Komm, Karline, komm! to the Amsterdam situation and retitled it: "Kom, Karline! kom!" (of "Wij gaan naar Tolhuis")
